com.epoch.responses

Class Response

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.responses.Response
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FormatConstants, QuestionConstants, XMLConstants

    public class Response
extends Object
implements FormatConstants, QuestionConstants
    Stores the student's response and parsed & processed versions of it. The purpose is to avoid repeated execution of the same processing steps for different evaluators.

        public Response(int qType,
                long qFlags,
                QDatum[] qData,
                EvalResult evalResult,
                Object[] substns,
                String[] userLangs,
                boolean maySee)
        Constructor called from Question.parseResponse().
        Parameters:
        qType - type of the question
        qFlags - flags of the question
        qData - question data of the question; required for energy diagrams and numeric responses
        evalResult - contains the student's response from the front end; uncolored version of student's response may be stored in the modifiedResponse field
        substns - R groups or variable values associated with this user's instance of the question; may be null or empty
        userLangs - languages chosen by this user in order of preference
        maySee - whether the user should be permitted to see calculated synthesis products in the feedback
